name: nytimes
text: Political Analysis: President Trump tries to project confidence in his final appeal to voters, but aides and allies tell @maggienyt, @jmartNYT and @alexburnsNYT that the potential consequences of losing the White House are never far from his mind. https://t.co/bQeimnj5Yw

name: nytimes
text: RT @mikiebarb: On today's Daily: On the eve of the Big Night, a viewer's guide to understanding election results as they roll in on Election Night. @alexburnsNYT with three potential scenarios. A must-listen for The Anxious: https://t.co/n8ehQbQrJt

name: nytimes
text: Ken Jennings, James Holzhauer and Brad Rutter will take turns appearing on an ABC revival of “The Chase,” a new version of a quiz show that airs in Britain, the network announced. https://t.co/6V7MS9NDcR

name: nytimes
text: RT @sheeraf: A deceptively-edited video of Biden that makes it seem as though he is claiming to have organized voter fraud has been viewed over 17 million times across social media. The response from Facebook, Twitter and YouTube has been all over the place: https://t.co/Ilzjs9rCCx

name: nytimes
text: The U.S. presidential race will be decided by voters in 12 competitive states. In this interactive diagram, you can assign electoral votes in those states to either candidate to see the possible outcomes. https://t.co/Hdr1Y4jfH6

name: nytimes
text: RT @nytmike: New voting story: The 100s of lawyers deployed is far beyond what has become normal since ‘00 election; is result of Trump/Rs efforts to disqualify votes on technicalities and baseless fraud charges. All comes as pandemic is severely testing voting system. https://t.co/rgU8QIKikb

name: nytimes
text:
An "I Voted" sticker is a must-have accessory to prove that you did, in fact, do your part.

Did you miss out this year?
Don't worry, we have a set of virtual ones for you to share.
https://t.co/oYcDeSmcmd

name: nytimes
text: RT @shearm: LEVERS OF POWER -- @realDonaldTrump and his aides have used the powers of incumbency in ways that go far beyond his predecessors, harnessing the levers of government power and the authority of Mr. Trump’s office to help him stay there. https://t.co/FHajwtODzO

name: nytimes
text: That Arizona is in play at all in the presidential race reflects remarkable changes in the state’s voting demographics. Only one Democrat — Bill Clinton in 1996 — has won the state since Harry Truman more than 70  years ago. https://t.co/0rkNIR4cBs

name: nytimes
text:
RT @hwise29: In this historic election, the act of voting has taken on extra significance for many Americans. 

The @nytimes wants your help to tell those stories. Tell us about your experience going to the polls: https://t.co/MjkRH4x1zG

text:

text: Californians are playing a major part in a historic surge in turnout across the country; the nation is on track to surpass 150 million votes for the first time. https://t.co/9s7qQnLk28

name: nytimes
text: RT @ewong: NEW: Top Trump officials are accused of using taxpayer resources to campaign for Trump — Pompeo, O’Brien, Barr, Wolf, Ratcliffe. Office of Special Counsel is investigating @SecPompeo for 2 potential illegal acts. w/ @shearm @michaelcrowley @KannoYoungs. https://t.co/jh8hnfEoD0

name: nytimes
text: The Georgia Supreme Court unanimously rejected a lower court’s decision to grant immunity to three former deputies in the death of Eurie Lee Martin, who was repeatedly tased. https://t.co/Ew7fOjKHMU

name: nytimes
text: Twitter and Facebook will warn users about election posts that prematurely declare victory. It is part of a series of steps that tech companies are implementing on Election Day to prevent the spread of misinformation. https://t.co/d4ewesZiAm
